A man and woman have been injured after two cars collided in Renfrewshire. Man and woman injured in Bridge of Weir road crash A man and woman have been injured after two cars collided in Renfrewshire.
Emergency services were called to the scene on A761 Kilmacolm Road, Bridge of Weir, at about 11:40 on Tuesday.
Fire crews used hydraulic equipment to cut the man free as paramedics treated him inside the car. He was taken to the Royal Alexandra Hospital in Paisley.
The woman who was driving the other car was also treated at the scene and taken to hospital. The road remains closed while police carry out investigations.
 